The paper discusses the use of machine learning classifiers for myoelectric control based on pattern recognition using EMG signals. This topic falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), robotics (cs.RO), and bioinformatics (cs.BIO). The paper also focuses on the classification of hand movements, which suggests a potential fit with the neural and evolutionary computing sub-category (cs.NE).
